    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe results of virtcol2col in Nvim 0.10 and Nvim 0.9.5 are inconsistent\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean test.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\n---你好\r\n\r\nprint(vim.fn.virtcol2col(0, 1, 3))\r\nprint(vim.fn.virtcol2col(0, 1, 4))\r\nprint(vim.fn.virtcol2col(0, 1, 5))\r\nprint(vim.fn.virtcol2col(0, 1, 6))\r\n```\r\n2. Run `:luafile %`\r\n\r\n- Nvim 0.9.5, the output is:\r\n```\r\n3\r\n6\r\n6\r\n9\r\n```\r\n- Nvim 0.10.0, the output is:\r\n```\r\n3\r\n4\r\n4\r\n7\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this is an \"intended\" change. But I think the result of Nvim 0.9.5 is correct.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0    NVIM v0.9.5  Release\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNot sure\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 11\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWindows Terminal\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nScoop",
