            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I simplified my use case; please refer to the video for details. From the highlighted area selected, virtcol2col should return the last byte.\r\n\r\nIf there is any misunderstanding or misuse on my part, please kindly point it out.\r\n\r\n```test.lua\r\n--------\r\n---你好\r\n--------\r\n\r\nvim.o.showmode = false\r\nlocal fn, api = vim.fn, vim.api\r\napi.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"CursorMoved\" }, {\r\n  group = api.nvim_create_augroup(\"test\", { clear = true }),\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    local mode = api.nvim_get_mode().mode\r\n    if mode ~= \"\\x16\" then\r\n      return\r\n    end\r\n    local start_vcol = fn.virtcol(\"v\")\r\n    local end_vcol = fn.virtcol(\".\")\r\n    local start_col = fn.virtcol2col(0, 2, start_vcol)\r\n    local end_col = fn.virtcol2col(0, 2, end_vcol)\r\n    -- print(start_col, end_col)\r\n    print(\"selected\", api.nvim_buf_get_text(0, 1, start_col - 1, 1, end_col, {})[1] or \"\")\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f77627b-2ec5-481f-b221-da2d8be7c755\r\n\r\n",
